<h2>Solar Incentives in Sacramento</h2>
<p>Sacramento residents have access to several valuable solar incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost, including equipment and installation, and remains at this level through 2032 before stepping down. California offers additional state-level incentives, including the California Solar Initiative and various rebate programs for qualifying installations. SMUD provides net energy metering (NEM) programs that allow solar customers to receive credit for excess electricity generated and fed back into the grid. Additionally, SMUD offers special time-of-use rates that can maximize savings for solar customers, and the utility occasionally provides rebates for battery storage systems when paired with solar installations. Property tax exemptions for solar installations mean that the added home value from solar panels won't increase property taxes, making the investment even more attractive for Sacramento homeowners.</p>

